values:
Yeah, so apparently there are&nbsp;a lot of Hilary lovers in KY, but that's okay.&nbsp;&nbsp;You know&nbsp;who I voted for!&nbsp; They said Barack got Jefferson Co (My hometown) so that makes me feel good.&nbsp; I headed out to the polls after work, and I was surprised to see only 2 other ladies in line!&nbsp; What?&nbsp; No big crowds?&nbsp;&nbsp;Did you know that KY hasn't voted in a primary in 40 years!!!??&nbsp; That in itself is Bullshit, they shouldn't stretch the voting process out so far if it isn't supposed to get to everyone.&nbsp; After voting I headed home to my boys.&nbsp; Tony hadn't even been home 5 mins.&nbsp; We relaxed a little and then popped in some games.&nbsp; He played Skate, I played Lost Odyssey (of course).&nbsp; Then I headed downstairs to fix some burritos!&nbsp; We bought some mexican cheese (I forget what kind)&nbsp;from the international section &amp; sour cream &amp; I made spanish rice.&nbsp; The rice turned out real tomatoey, but we piled it on and devoured it!

After din din we watched some boob tube.&nbsp; More playoffs, though I can't remember who won, we watched the celtics play.&nbsp; I crocheted another diamond.&nbsp; I thought I had enough of my skeen left, but ran out about 4 rows from the end, so I tied the new skeen to it.&nbsp; Though the color code is the same, there is a slight difference in color.&nbsp; I don't think you would notice if someone didn't point it out, but I am not surprised considering I started &amp; bought the original yarn almost 10 years ago.&nbsp; he he&nbsp; I am determined to get this thing done, I am just missing one color.&nbsp; But I want to check out their site, and surely you can buy yarn there.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Well, that's all for now folks!&nbsp;
